# pyenv
#   For a library or app, you might want to share your .python-version.
#   Reference: https://github.com/pyenv/pyenv/blob/master/COMMANDS.md#pyenv-version
#.python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if having platform-specific dependencies or dependencies
#   having no cross-platform support, pipenv may install dependencies that don’t work, or even fail.
#Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, poetry.lock contains the exact dependency versions and should be checked in.
#Poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, pdm.lock contains the exact dependency versions and should be checked in.
#pdm.lock

